        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:38PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 338 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gregory, or 8 miles east of Taft, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Portland, Rockport, Port Aransas, Taft, Ingleside, Aransas Pass,
Gregory, Ingleside On The Bay, Bayside, Palm Harbor, Key Allegro,
Fulton, and Taft Southwest.

This includes US Highway 181 between mile markers 628 and 644.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
